{"name":"Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Integral.RieszMarkovKakutani","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Topology.ContinuousFunction.Bounded","Mathlib.Topology.Sets.Compacts"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/RieszMarkovKakutani.lean#L98-L116","name":"rieszContentAux_sup_le","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/RieszMarkovKakutani.html#rieszContentAux_sup_le","doc":"The Riesz content λ associated to a given positive linear functional Λ is\nfinitely subadditive: `λ(K₁ ∪ K₂) ≤ λ(K₁) + λ(K₂)` for any compact subsets `K₁, K₂ ⊆ X`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/RieszMarkovKakutani.lean#L85-L93","name":"exists_lt_rieszContentAux_add_pos","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/RieszMarkovKakutani.html#exists_lt_rieszContentAux_add_pos","doc":"The Riesz content can be approximated arbitrarily well by evaluating the positive linear\nfunctional on test functions: for any `ε > 0`, there exists a bounded continuous nonnegative\nfunction f on X such that `f ≥ 1` on K and such that `λ(K) ≤ Λ f < λ(K) + ε`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/RieszMarkovKakutani.lean#L77-L79","name":"rieszContentAux_le","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/RieszMarkovKakutani.html#rieszContentAux_le","doc":"Any bounded continuous nonnegative f such that `f ≥ 1` on K gives an upper bound on the\ncontent of K; namely `λ(K) ≤ Λ f`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/RieszMarkovKakutani.lean#L65-L68","name":"rieszContentAux_mono","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/RieszMarkovKakutani.html#rieszContentAux_mono","doc":"Riesz content λ (associated with a positive linear functional Λ) is\nmonotone: if `K₁ ⊆ K₂` are compact subsets in X, then `λ(K₁) ≤ λ(K₂)`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/RieszMarkovKakutani.lean#L55-L60","name":"riesz_content_aux_image_nonempty","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/RieszMarkovKakutani.html#riesz_content_aux_image_nonempty","doc":"For any compact subset `K ⊆ X`, there exist some bounded continuous nonnegative\nfunctions f on X such that `f ≥ 1` on K. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/RieszMarkovKakutani.lean#L47-L48","name":"rieszContentAux","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/RieszMarkovKakutani.html#rieszContentAux","doc":"Given a positive linear functional Λ on X, for `K ⊆ X` compact define\n`λ(K) = inf {Λf | 1≤f on K}`. When X is a compact Hausdorff space, this will be shown to be a\ncontent, and will be shown to agree with the Riesz measure on the compact subsets `K ⊆ X`. "}]}